place the  testassignment  file  in the user's folder

change to the user's folder(say the home directory of the user) i.e.  cd  ~

change the file permissions to the desired effect

say  chmod 755  testassignement

run the script  as shown below

./testassignment   or  /bin/bash   ~/testassignmentp

then

the user is prompted with the Menu and asked to choose a menu-option,
based on the option choosen the particular command is run and after the running the menu-option
returns back to the Menu ...this process is repeated until the user choose's the option or choice 8
when the loop is broken and the program exits and control is returned to the shell prompt.
